 1 comprises the analysis, debates and outcomes, together with ten primary documents relating to the years 1945–1999, as well as a bibliography and index. Volume 2 comprises a further 34 documents relating to the years 2000–2020, including international covenants, US Trafficking In Persons and Congressional reports, and Japanese government papers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aHuman rights advocacyzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aHuman rightszJapanxHistoryy20th century. 0aHuman traffickingzJapanxHistoryy20th century. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Human Rights.2bisacsh  aHuman trafficking.  adomestic and international trafficking.  aforced labour.  amodern slavery.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311068955640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781912961139?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781912961139423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781912961139/original  a978-3-11-068955-6  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK